headline: Lowe’s, SoFi, Carvana: Stocks That Defined the Week
content: Lowe’s said its sales growth will ease this year but projected that its profitability will improve, a day after its larger competitor  Home Depot  gave a similar sales outlook for 2022.  Lowe’s shares added 0.2% Wednesday.  SoFi  a lender that once wanted to take business from banks, is doubling down on its new life as a bank.

headline: U.S. Stocks Rally to Finish Turbulent Week
content: Investors shifted bets on how the Fed will proceed with rate increases in the wake of Russia’s invasion of Ukraine.

headline: Dish stock rallies to best day in nearly two years after double upgrade
content: Shares of Dish Network Corp. extended their rally Friday to finish with their best performance in nearly two years as the telecommunications company won over a former Wall Street skeptic.

headline: Dow Jones Futures: Market Rally Continues Amid Russia's Ukraine Invasion; Apple Leads 5 Stocks Setting Up
content: A market rally attempt during Russia's Ukraine invasion has a lot to prove. But investors should get ready.

headline: Molina Healthcare to join the S&P 500 index
content: S&P Dow Jones Indices said late Friday that Molina Healthcare Inc. will join the S&P 500 index , replacing IHS Markit Ltd , which is being acquired by S&P Global Inc. , an S&P 500 constituent. Energy company Range Resources Corp. will replace Molina Healthcare in the S&P MidCap 400. The changes are effective Wednesday before the bell. The IHS Markit deal is expected to be completed Monday.

headline: Why Stocks Rebounded After Russia Invaded Ukraine
content: It looks like traders are judging that Ukraine won’t be that bad for Wall Street for now, but expect markets to keep swinging about as reality intrudes.

headline: 5 Best Chinese Stocks To Buy And Watch
content: Hundreds of Chinese companies are listed on U.S. markets. But which are the best Chinese stocks to buy or watch right now? JD.com , NetEase, Li Auto, Xpeng and BYD Co.. China is the world's most-populous nation and the second-largest economy with a booming urban middle class and amazing entrepreneurial activity.

headline: Denver’s office market shows strong signs of bouncing back from pandemic, report says
content: In CBRE's monthly office pulse report, Denver's score shows that the office market might be returning in the Mile High City.

headline: RIO Stock A Bright Spot In Ailing Market
